title: Grateful Dead Live at UIC Pavilion, Chicago, IL on 1987-04-09
lineage: MC (XLII 90+100) > Nak Dragon > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) > EZ CD Audio Converter > PCM @ 2496
description:
The Grateful Dead
UIC Pavilion
Chicago, IL
1987-04-09

Source:   2x Nak 300 CP4 + 1x Nak 300 (center) > unknown mixer > Nak 550 by Barry Levitt
Transfer: MC (XLII 90+100) > Nak Dragon > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) > EZ CD Audio Converter > PCM @ 2496
Master:   Wavelab 12 (tracking, fades, patching, pitch correction, resample, Lin dither) > FLAC 1644

Thanks to Barry for taping, Liza for preserving his collection, and Ted Mattes for facilitating

Set I
01. crowd
02. Greatest Story
03. Promised Land
04. When Push Comes To Shove
05. Never Trust A Woman
06. El Paso
07. Row Jimmy
08. Brother Esau
09. Far From Me
10. Deal

Set II
11. crowd
12. Scarlet Begonias >
13. Fire On The Mountain >
14. Playin' In The Band >
15. Uncle John's Band >
16. drums >
17. space >
18. China Doll >
19. Playin' Reprise >
20. Sugar Magnolia >
21. Sunshine Daydream
22. crowd

Encore:
23. U.S. Blues

From the collection of Barry Levitt.   His collection of cassettes, DATs and PCM was saved from the dump and stored by his ex, Liza, for many years until it was rescued from a storage shed in New Jersey.  Many of his tapes, including this one, have not been seen or heard for nearly 30 years.

Patched with, and pitch corrected against, https://etreedb.org/shn/148863

Enjoy!

--mhg :: 2025-03-23
